headline.main: Dwight David Eisenhower: A Leader in War and Peace

abstract: obituary; career in pol, army, as elder statemen living in retirement; H W Baldwin appraisal of him as gen; illus of scenes from his life
snippet: MILITARY leadership of the victorious Allied forces in Western Europe during World War II invested Dwight David Eisenhower with an immense popularity, almost amounting to devotion, that twice elected him President of the United States.
